article.description: — David DeJulius had 21 points as Cincinnati rolled past Alabama A&M 89-66 on Tuesday night.
article.headline: DeJulius lifts Cincinnati over Alabama A&M 89-66
article.linkText: DeJulius lifts Cincinnati over Alabama A&M 89-66
article.story: CINCINNATI -- — David DeJulius had 21 points as Cincinnati rolled past Alabama A&M 89-66 on Tuesday night. Mike Saunders Jr. had 14 points for Cincinnati (3-0). Ody Oguama added 13 points and eight rebounds. Jeremiah Davenport had 12 points. Jalen Johnson scored a career-high 30 points and had seven rebounds for the Bulldogs (1-2). Garrett Hicks added 11 points and Eric Lee had six rebounds. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
